data.name: DescriptionAttribute_CodeStyle
data.value: Style used for the lines of code when line numbers or alternate lines are not enabled.

data.name: DescriptionAttribute_AspStyle
data.value: Style used for lines containing ASP code.

data.name: DescriptionAttribute_RunSilent
data.value: Flag indicating whether or not to run in silent mode. Silent mode allows for the quick pasting of formatted source code using the last configuration.

data.name: DescriptionAttribute_WordWrap
data.value: Flag indicating whether word-wrapping is enabled in the view.

data.name: DescriptionAttribute_AltevenStyle
data.value: Style used for the even alternating lines of code.

data.name: DescriptionAttribute_AttrStyle
data.value: Style used for attributes in HTML code.

data.name: DescriptionAttribute_ActiveMode
data.value: View mode driving the layout of the Code Snippet dialog. It can be either Compact or Full.

data.name: DescriptionAttribute_ActiveView
data.value: Active view type driving the main workspace area of the Code Snippet dialog. It can be one of CodeSnippet, FormattedCodeSnippet, or Both.

data.name: RunningSilent
data.value:
Run Silent mode will cause the plugin to process the contents of the clipboard without displaying the dialog. Once enabled, the plugin will perform all processing in the background. The processing will be done with the latest settings configured.
To turn off Run Silent mode, hold down the 'Ctrl' key while executing the command that launches the plugin. Continue holding until the dialog appears.
If you enable Run Silent mode this dialog instance will close and any in-process data will be discarded. You will need to execute the request again.
Are you sure you want to enable Run Silent mode?

data.name: DescriptionAttribute_AlternateLines
data.value: Flag indicating whether or not lines will have alternating background colors.

data.name: DescriptionAttribute_SectionName
data.value: Name of the section being viewed.

data.name: DescriptionAttribute_AltStyle
data.value: Style used for the odd alternating lines of code.

data.name: DescriptionAttribute_PreStyle
data.value: Style used for the lines of code when line numbers or alternate lines are enabled.

data.name: CopyStyles
data.value:
The CSS styles used in this plugin have been copied to the Clipboard. You can now paste them in your Blog's master template or in one of your style files that is loaded as part of your blog.
Make sure to clear the Embed Styles option to ensure the main styles are used. Otherwise, the styles will always be embedded and they will override modifications you may have made to customize the layout of code snippets.

data.name: DescriptionAttribute_UseContainer
data.value: Flag indicating whether or not to use a container for the generated code.

data.name: DescriptionAttribute_EmbedStyles
data.value: Flag indicating whether or not the CSS styles used will be embedded with the HTML output.

data.name: DescriptionAttribute_TrimIndentOnPaste
data.value: Flag indicating whether or not to trim TAB characters from the beginning of lines when being pasted.

data.name: DescriptionAttribute_TabSpaces
data.value: Number of space characters to substitute for tab characters.

data.name: DescriptionAttribute_WrapperStyle
data.value: Style used for the wrapping container of the code snippet.

data.name: ProcessSelectedTextAsCodeSnippet
data.value:
The selected text is not recognized as a code snippet previously generated by the plugin. However, you may still attempt to load the text to process as a code snippet.
Would you like to treat the selected text as a code snippet and edit it?

data.name: DescriptionAttribute_Styles
data.value: Cascading style sheet definitions for different code snippet styles.

data.name: DescriptionAttribute_LineNumbers
data.value: Flag indicating whether or not line numbers are generated.
